Since the Occupy Wall Street protests set up shop, heaps of smaller occupations have cropped up throughout the nation. The motion includes extra than 1,300 groups, in accordance to the Occupy Together website.
Beth Leech, a political science professor at Rutgers University, said the growth of Occupy Wall Street mirrors the civil rights movement, which unfold from the Southern Leadership Council to copycat sit-ins and protests across the nation. "Youll see replication of whats came about in one location occur in another," Leech said. "These are people who are upset for a range of reasons. Theyre coming out to express their frustration relatively organically."


