The protesters set up camp in Trenton on Thursday, complete with drowsing bags, symptoms bemoaning company greed and particular areas: "administration," "art," "comfort" and "sanitation." About a dozen slept at the memorial Monday night, and extra have shown up every day. The protesters are assured their movement will grow.
